@page "/secondsoft"

<style>
    :root {
        --fontColor: white;
        --fontSize: 0.85rem;
    }

    body {
        background-color: #222B31 !important;
    }

    header a {
        color: var(--fontColor);
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 900;
    }

    #wrapper {
        color: var(--fontColor);
    }

    .content {
        background-color: #222B31 !important;
        color: whitesmoke !important;
        font-family: "Source Sans Pro", Helvetica, sans-serif;
    }

    h2, .link {
        background-color: transparent !important;
        color: whitesmoke !important;
    }

    .link {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    #content {
        padding: 0 40px;
    }
</style>

<PageTitle>About this website</PageTitle>

<!-- Wrapper -->
<div id="wrapper">
    <header id="header">
        <a href="secondsoft">My own <br /> blazor showcase</a>
    </header>
    <div class="upperblock maintext">About this website</div>

    <!-- Main -->
    <div id="content">
        <br />
        <p>
            On this company and portfolio site, I try to showcase beautiful technologies created using only Blazor, HTML, and CSS.<br />
            With these examples I will show you the power that Blazor has to let you program a web application correctly.<br />
            <br />
            This web app runs on the Blazor server. <br />
        </p>

        <div style="float:left; margin-left:1rem;"><a @onclick="() => Details(1)" style="text-decoration:underline">Example 1 Contact component <i class="fa-solid fa-square-caret-down"></i></a></div>
        <div style="float:left; margin-left:1rem;"><a @onclick="() => Details(2)" style="text-decoration:underline">Example 2 Project overview components <i class="fa-solid fa-square-caret-down"></i></a></div>
        <div style="float:left; margin-left:1rem;"><a @onclick="() => Details(3)" style="text-decoration:underline">Example 3 Security <i class="fa-solid fa-square-caret-down"></i></a></div>
        <br />
        <div hidden="@ShowExample1">
            <br />
            The contact component is a great example of what you can do with Blazor.<br/>
            The component is simply used on multiple pages with all text white and background transparent by <br /> parameters
            <br />
            On this component you can change colors, such as the background, to gold, as shown below.<br />
            <br />
            
            <Contactpage colors="white/dark goldenrod"></Contactpage>
            
            
            And it even gets better.
        </div>
        <div hidden="@ShowExample2">
            <br />
            I made an overview component for each project <br />

            Those pages are used in the SampleBlocks on the <a target="_blank" class="link" href="portfolio">Portfolio page &nbsp; <i class="fa-solid fa-up-right-from-square"></i></a> and the carousel on the<a class="link" target="_blank" href="/"> homepage &nbsp; <i class="fa-solid fa-up-right-from-square"></i></a><br />
            <img style="max-height:4em;" src="./images/showcase/samplepages.jpg" />&nbsp; <img style="max-height:4em;" src="./images/showcase/samplecarousel.jpg" /><br />
            Since all pages are responsive, I still had to scale the pages for the carousel with a parameter to 70%.<br />
            <br />
            The project pages are without background. If you visit them natively, they don't look so nice.<br />
            <a target="_blank" class="link" href="secondsoftOverview">Secondsoft Overview page &nbsp; <i class="fa-solid fa-up-right-from-square"></i></a><br />
            <a target="_blank" class="link" href="secondlogOverview">Secondlog Overview page &nbsp; <i class="fa-solid fa-up-right-from-square"></i></a><br />
            <a target="_blank" class="link" href="MicroportalOverview">Microportal Overview page &nbsp; <i class="fa-solid fa-up-right-from-square"></i></a><br />
            <a target="_blank" class="link" href="BarmateOverview">Barmate Overview page &nbsp; <i class="fa-solid fa-up-right-from-square"></i></a><br />
            <a target="_blank" class="link" href="FitmateOverview">Fitmate Overview page &nbsp; <i class="fa-solid fa-up-right-from-square"></i></a><br />
            With a ligth background, by design all text becomes black and all other behavior will be done with Parameters.
        </div>
        <div hidden="@ShowExample3">
            <br />
            Under construction !!!
        </div>
        <br />
        <br />
        <Contact mycolor="white" />
        <br />
        <br />
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    private bool ShowExample1 { get; set; } = true;
    private bool ShowExample2 { get; set; } = true;
    private bool ShowExample3 { get; set; } = true;
    private void Details(int exNumber)
    {
        ShowExample1 = !(exNumber == 1);
        ShowExample2 = !(exNumber == 2);
        ShowExample3 = !(exNumber == 3);
    }
}
